answers.body_markdown:
`createGameCardsArray` creates an array of references to the *same instance* of `items[random index]`, so editing the card from one reference would reflect the change in all references to the same card. The solution is to clone each card with the [spread operator](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Operators/Spread_syntax#Spread_in_object_literals) (or [`Object.assign`](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/assign)):

```js
function createGameCardsArray() {
  const cards = [];
  for (let i = 0; i &lt;= 17; i++) {
    cards[i] = { ...items[Math.floor(Math.random() * 6)] };
  }
  return cards;
}
```

